    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Combination Meter Removal and Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not leave or work on the meter with the dial down for long periods of time as this may cause malfunction.",
        "When replacing a combination meter with a new one, use HDS to read out the odometer data before replacement."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Od Data Read",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R001028",
          "label": "Od Data Read",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Meter panel removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000770",
          "label": "Meter panel removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Meter assembly removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1029_3.0_jpn_11580926_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the screw (A). Place a rag on the steering column cover and pull out the meter assembly (B). Disconnect the coupler (C). Remove the meter assembly, taking care not to damage any parts of the meter."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Od Data Write",
